---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro"
import Button from "@components/Button.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Plugins & Client Mods"
  description="Use Shelter or Vencord with Legcord for Discord themes, custom CSS, and plugins. No injectors—enable in Legcord settings."
  canonical="/plugins"
>
  <article class="bg-gray-900 py-16" aria-labelledby="plugins-heading">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <header class="text-center mb-10">
        <h1 id="plugins-heading" class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
          <span class="bg-clip-text text-transparent bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-200 to-purple-300">Plugins & client mods</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-4 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Legcord supports <strong class="text-gray-300">client mods</strong> (plugins) that add Discord themes, custom CSS, and extra features. Enable or switch between them in <strong class="text-gray-300">Settings → Legcord</strong>. No separate installers or injectors are needed.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Both <strong class="text-gray-400">Shelter</strong> and <strong class="text-gray-400">Vencord</strong> work with Legcord. Use one at a time to avoid conflicts. See the <a href="/faq" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">FAQ</a> for more on the difference between them.
        </p>
      </header>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-6 text-center">Choose your client mod</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12">
        <Button name="Shelter" href="https://shelter.uwu.network/plugins" description="Comes with every Legcord install" />
        <Button name="Vencord" href="https://vencord.dev/plugins#" description="Togglable in Legcord settings" />
      </div>
      <section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-700/50" aria-labelledby="plugins-tips">
        <h2 id="plugins-tips" class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3">Tips for using Discord plugins with Legcord</h2>
        <ul class="text-gray-400 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">•</span>
            Shelter is the default client mod and is recommended for most users.
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">•</span>
            Themes and plugins are managed inside each mod's own settings or plugin list.
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">•</span>
            Legcord developers are not affiliated with Shelter or Vencord. Only Shelter is officially supported with Legcord.
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">•</span>
            If something breaks after adding a plugin, try disabling it or switching mods.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>